Some products exist that allow front end code to create query filters/criteria without rendering those queries in the source code through various conditional statements, string concatenation, etc. It might be programmatically safer to create a series of small objects than it is to piece together a potentially long string.

One possible use case in PuppetBoard: Instead of building one query based on a '*' environment and another one based on everything else create the necessary binary operator object(s) and append them to a parent boolean operator object.

My idea is to have a code structure as follows:

```
class BooleanOperator(object):
    ...
class AndOperator(BooleanOperator):
    ...
class OrOperator(BooleanOperator):
    ...
class NotOperator(BooleanOperator):
    ...

class BinaryOperator(object):
    ...
class EqualsOperator(BinaryOperator):
    ...
class GreaterOperator(BinaryOperator):
    ...
class LessOperator(BinaryOperator):
    ...
class GraterEqualOperator(BinaryOperator):
    ...
```

